This is definitely a game you can play again and again without ever getting tired of.

content: I've never played a game like this before; it's as unique and beautiful as it is heartbreaking. Even without knowing the back story, it seemed like something I would like, but I wasn't prepared for the narrative. My grandmother, one of only two people in my family who I have a relationship with, was diagnosed with primary progressive aphasia, and it feels like I'm reading her future. A very hard pill to swallow. Anyways, thank you.
